CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 18, 1961, pg. 2, reads: "HIRED AT BAKER'S - Offering courteous service to a customer is Walter Wray, who recently was hired as a shoe salesman by Baker's Shoe Store in East Liberty, as a result of intensive picketing and negotiations by local NAACP officials. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Shoe salesman Walter Wray fitting shoes on seated female customer in Baker's Shoe Store, East Liberty
